<TITLE> Parliament reconvenes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com)Parliament reconvened on Sunday after a two-day recess. It got down to business around 4pm with speaker Abdul Hamid in the chair. The budget session of the ninth parliament began on June 2, with the main opposition BNP walking out of parliament twice and not attending parliament the following day. Finance minister A M A Muhith is set to table the national budget for 2010-11 financial year on June 10. BNP will set out its views and proposals on the budget at an event at Dhaka Sheraton Hotel on Monday afternoon presided over by chairperson Khaleda Zia. Political leaders, economists, businessmen, intellectuals, editors of national dailies, professionals, civil society representatives and envoys of foreign missions have been invited to the programme. 
